Class
Description
Auth
Handles reading and writing the all of the users API Keys required for BTTN.

The main function for BTTN which passes arguments and controls the flow of BTTN
Bundle
Helps with getting the user's current language and deciding which resource bundle to use

Class that holds the data for each channel and helps with adding and removing channels
Failover
Function that manages setting up the failover method and building the failover message to be sent
Helper
Class that holds helper functions used throughout the program
Logging
Helps with logging all messages to the log file and clear the log when needed
Notifications
Sends all the notification used throughout BTTN and handles sending failover notification if needed
SetupManager
Class that manages the program when in setup mode, and controls the flow of the program
Updater
Determines if an update is available and when to send a notification alerting of the update!
